  "text": "Now we consider integration on the deformed disk. In [CITATION_1] an integral is given which has classical limit the Lebesgue integral on the unit disk, and is subsequently used to examine noncommutative function theory on the disk. However we use another integral with U q (su 1,1 ) invariance. A partially defined map ∫ ∶ C q [D] → C, invariant for the U q (su 1,1 ) action, is defined by",
